The paper discusses the behavioural theory of concurrent systems and how it can be captured by concurrent Abstract State Machines (cASMs) with shared memory. This topic falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses messaging between agents and the effects of different replication policies, which are topics related to Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Software Engineering (cs.SE). The use of cASMs also involves the study of formal methods and verification, which falls under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO).
